apology /əˈpɒlədʒɪ/

(apologies) 

1. N-VAR An apology is something that you say or write in order to tell someone that you are sorry that you have hurt them or caused trouble for them. 表达歉意的言辞 

例： I didn't get an apology. 我没有得到道歉之词。 

例： We received a letter of apology. 我们收到了一封致歉信。 

2. N-PLURAL If you offer or make your apologies , you apologize. (表达) 歉意 [正式] 

例： When Mary finally appeared, she made her apologies to Mrs. Velasquez. 当玛丽最终露面时，她向委拉斯开兹夫人道了歉。

